<DOC><DOCNO> AP890105-0104 </DOCNO><FILEID>AP-NR-01-05-89 1239EST</FILEID><FIRST>r i AM-BRF--BritishRail     01-05 0145</FIRST><SECOND>AM-BRF--British Rail,0149</SECOND><HEAD>British Rail to Pay 10,000 Pounds Compensation for Crash</HEAD><DATELINE>LONDON (AP) </DATELINE><TEXT>   British Rail will pay about $18,000 in immediatecompensation to relatives of the 34 people killed in last month'sClapham rail crash, officials said Thursday.   The sum would be given in advance of consideration for otherpossible compensation awards following the Dec. 12 disaster, said aspokesman for the state-run rail service.   ``In many cases, this payment for bereavement will be only partof the overall compensation paid,'' said the spokesman.   British Rail also offered families $3,600 in hardshipcompensation immediately following the triple-train crash in southLondon.   The morning rush-hour crash injured more than 100 people andkilled 33 others outright. Another victim died later of injuries.   British Rail said that improperly installed signal equipmentduring a modernization of signals probably caused the accident, butis still investigating.</TEXT></DOC>